steps.section: Procedure for the preparation of adherent tumor cells (target cells) for ELISA and CellTrace assays
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8d9mb","text":"In new 15mL tubes, prepare 1.5×106 cells / 6mL mTCM in 15mL tubes; irradiate the cell lines with 100Gy (10,000 rad) in a Cesium irradiator.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":33,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Procedure for the preparation of adherent tumor cells (target cells) for ELISA and CellTrace assays
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8ld5l","text":"For the ELISA plate: pipet 100μL (2.5×104) of the target cells to 96-well plate wells. For no-target controls, use 100μL mTCM. For positive control, use 100μL of 2X PMA/Iono stimulation cocktail (eBioscience).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":40,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cmnma","text":"Harvest the transduced mouse T cells (see protocol titled \"Retroviral transduction of primary murine CD8 T cells\" for details) and transfer them to a 15mL falcon tube. Centrifuge cells at 400rcf for 6mins; resuspend in 1mL mTCM; count; prepare 3×106 T cells / 6mL mTCM in a new tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":248,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4qa52","text":"Aliquot 100 μL (5×104 cells) to the respective wells in 96-well “ELISA” plates; mark the time; place at 37C for 24 hr. Save 4mL (2×106 T cells) for CellTrace labeling (see below).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":20,"length":1},{"style":"sup","offset":133,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Procedure for the preparation of adherent tumor cells (target cells) for ELISA and CellTrace assays
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"84jpq","text":"Create a mirror-image of the 96-well plate for the \"CellTrace\" plate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6nisq","text":"Meanwhile, with the hood lights turned off, prepare a 1:1000 CellTrace solution in PBS (consult the manufacturer's protcol for detailed instructions). Prepare enough volume to label 1e6 cells / mL.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"87ctd","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2v93","text":"Add 10mL PBS to each 4mL T cell suspension; centrifuge at 400rcf for 6mins; resuspend cells are 1e6 / mL CellTrace solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"10oi9","text":"Incubate in the 37ºC incubator for 20 mins. Then quench with five times the staining volume and incubate  in the 37ºC incubator for an additional 5 mins. Centrifuge at 400rcf for 6mins; resuspend in 4mL mTCM.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2dpg0","text":"After 24 hours, carefully harvest 100 uL from each well without disturbing the pellets. The supernatant can then be frozen at -20C until the samples are required to perform the ELISA.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d3khd","text":"Distribute 100μL aliquots (5×104 cells) to the labeled wells of “CellTrace” plate. Wrap plate in foil; mark the time; place in the incubator for 48 hr. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":31,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"706b","text":"At 48 hrs, gently mix the effector cells before transfering the samples to a new U-bottom 96 well plate. Immunophenotype the samples with the appropriate markers (e.g. CD8, transduction marker, congenic marker, etc..). Attention should be given to the spectral overlap between the respective CellTrace reagent used and the markers used in staining.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
